{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf949\cocoasubrtf330 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Overview\ \
\b0 Support for instructor to quickly delete messages in a forum. The current process for deleting messages is cumbersome for instructors that need to delete a large amount of messages at once. \b \ \ Use Cases\ \
\b0 1) An instructor notices that the majority of the messages that have been posted to a particular thread are off topic and he wants to delete the thread and recreate it.\ \ 2) An instructor is cleaning up a thread and getting rid of irrelevant messages and messages that do not contribute substantially to the thread.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf949\cocoasubrtf330 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Notes\ \ Instructor clicked Delete Forum on FH-1:\
\b0 - If an instructor clicks the "Delete" button, the forum and all associated topics and messages will be deleted and the system will return the instructor to the Forums Home screen (FH-1).\ - If an instructor clicks the "Cancel" button, the system will cancel the delete action and return the instructor to the Forums Home screen (FH-1).\ \
\b Instructor clicked Delete Forum on IFV-1:\
\b0 - If an instructor clicks the "Delete" button, the forum and all associated topics and messages will be deleted and the system will return the instructor to the Forums Home screen (FH-1).\ - If an instructor clicks the "Cancel" button, the system will cancel the delete action and return the instructor to the Individual Forum View screen (IFV-1).}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf949\cocoasubrtf330 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Notes\ \ Instructor clicked Delete Topic on FH-1:\
\b0 - If an instructor clicks the "Delete" button, the topic and all associated messages will be deleted and the system will return the instructor to the Forums Home screen (FH-1).\ - If an instructor clicks the "Cancel" button, the system will cancel the delete action and return the instructor to the Forums Home screen (FH-1).\ \
\b Instructor clicked Delete Topic on IFV-1:\
\b0 - If an instructor clicks the "Delete" button, the topic and all associated messages will be deleted and the system will return the instructor to the Individual Forum View screen (IFV-1).\ - If an instructor clicks the "Cancel" button, the system will cancel the delete action and return the instructor to the Individual Forum View screen (IFV-1).}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf949\cocoasubrtf330 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Notes\ \
\b0 If an instructor deletes a thread, the parent message and all associated child messages will be deleted. A placeholder will remain for the parent message and the thread's subject will be replaced by the text "Deleted by <Name of User who Deleted Thread>". Beneath this text, in parentheses, the system will display "Deleted <Date and Time Thread was Deleted>".\ \ Also, the system will include a "Restore Thread" link. \ \ - If an instructor clicks the "Restore Thread" link, the system will restore the parent message and all associated child messages.\ \
\b Note: \b0 The restored parent message and all associated child messages will retain the same unread status they had prior to being deleted.\ \ - If an instructor clicks the "Hide Deleted Messages" link, the system will remove the deleted messages from this view and change the "Hide Deleted Messages" link to "Show Deleted Messages". \ \
\b Note: \b0 The "Hide Deleted Messages" link will only be displayed if one or more messages have been deleted.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf949\cocoasubrtf330 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Notes\ \
\b0 If an instructor deletes a message, a placeholder will remain for the message and the subject of the message will be replaced by the text "Deleted by <Name of User who Deleted Message>". Beneath this text, in parentheses, the system will display "Deleted <Date and Time Thread was Deleted>"\ \ Also, the system will include a "Restore" link. \ \ - If an instructor clicks the "Restore" link next to a deleted message, the system will restore the message. \
\b \ Note: \b0 The restored message will retain the same unread status it had prior to being deleted.\ \ - If an instructor clicks the "Hide Deleted Messages" link, the system will remove the deleted messages from this view and change the "Hide Deleted Messages" link to "Show Deleted Messages". \ \
\b Note: \b0 The "Hide Deleted Messages" link will only be displayed if one or more messages have been deleted.}
